<h1>Download and Installation</h1>
Current version: 0.9.2 (19 June 2007) - post ASM 2007<br/>
<br/>
We have initially released our binary files on our web site. We plan to use the release system of SourceForge only later this year.<br/>
<h2>Command Line version</h2>
<h3>Prerequisites</h3>
<p><strong>Java</strong>: Asmeta tools need Java &gt;= 1.5.0 to run. </p>
<h3>Download</h3>
<p>Download the parser: <a
 href="http://svn.code.sf.net/p/asmeta/code/code/stable/parser_cli/AsmetaLc.jar">
AsmetaLc.jar</a></p>
<p>Download the interpreter: <a href="http://svn.code.sf.net/p/asmeta/code/code/stable/interpreter_cli/AsmetaS.jar">
AsmetaS.jar</a></p>
<h3>How to run (see <a href="userdoc/tools.html">userdoc/tools.html</a> for instructions)</h3>
<p>To run the parser - in <strong>brief</strong></p>
<pre>java -jar AsmetaLc.jar &lt;filename&gt;</pre>
To run the ASM simulator <span style="font-weight: bold;">- in brief</span>
<pre>java -jar AsmetaS.jar &lt;filename&gt;</pre>
<h2>Eclipse interface ASMEE </h2>
A <strong>graphical front-end</strong> called ASMEE (ASM Eclipse Environment) which allows to edit and manipulate AsmM models. This environment is implemented as an <a href="http://www.eclipse.org/">Eclipse</a> plug-in.
<h3>Prerequisites</h3>
<p>You need the last version of eclipse.</p>
<h3>Option 1.&nbsp;Update Site</h3>
<p>The update site for Asmee is <b>http://svn.code.sf.net/p/asmeta/code/code/stable/asmee_update/</b>.
Perform the following steps to install Asmee from the update site: </p>
<p><b>1. From your Eclipse menu select <i>Help</i> &#8594; <i>Software
Updates</i> &#8594;
<i>Find and Install...</i></b> </p>
<p><b>2. Check <i>Search for new features</i> and press <i>Next</i>.</b>
</p>
<p><b>3. Press <i>New Remote Site...</i> and enter
http://svn.code.sf.net/p/asmeta/code/code/stable/asmee_update/ for the update site URL:</b> </p>
<p><b>4. Press <i>Finish</i>.</b> </p>
<p><b>5. Follow the steps in the installation wizard.</b> </p>
<h3>Option 2. Manual Installation</h3>
<p>Download <a href="http://fmse.di.unimi.it/asmeta/download/asmee_site.zip">asmee_site.zip</a> which contains a zipped version of the asmee update site. Unzip it and copy it in a temporary directory (for example c:\temp\asmee). Then update eclipse like in Option 1, except that in step 3 choose new Local Site and select the directory (c:\temp\asmee) where you have unzipped the asmee_site.</p>
